reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very effective vitamins
reviews.reviewText: I had major vitamin deficiencies as an adult. My internist told me to take two of these every day. Within just a few months, my deficiencies were resolved, and I was feeling better. These are easy to swallow and definitely effective. They did not upset my stomach like many vitamins for adults. They are chewable for folks who have trouble swallowing large pills. They also have much higher vitamin levels than their gummy counterparts. I do wish the flavor was a bit better. I seem to recall these vitamins tasting much better even five or ten years ago, but I read something online about a change in the way they were made, which may have affected their taste. They are a bit expensive compared to some other brands, but I've ended up continuing to use them because they have not bothered my stomach and are definitely working.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Just like when I was younger
reviews.reviewText: These still taste great. I prefer them to other multivitamins cause they don't upset my stomach.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Not as Tasty as the +Iron Flintstones
reviews.reviewText: Gastric Bypass patient here who needs a chewable multivitamin everyday. I was taking the ones with Iron for a long time and it was like a little treat every morning. I had too much iron and was switched to these without the added iron and unfortunately, I don't feel like I have my little sweet piece of candy every morning anymore. These Flintstones are not as flavorful as the others, but are still edible, so I can't knock them too much. My vitamin levels are good, so they must be doing the job!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 18, 2023
reviews.reviewText: We used these same vitamin type as a kid and now my kids love taking them as well. They are easy to chew tablets so they do not stick to the teeth like gummy vitamins do. Having no sugar in them is also good.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 24, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I just had surgery and Flintstone viatmains were recommended 2/day since they were chewable. First time I took one, it instantly brought me back to my youth when I took these. Taste the same as they did 40 yrs ago. Great product. Great price on Amazon compared to local stores. Would definitely buy again.
